n ever before. Some market participants, such as principal-trading firms (P=
TFs) that use high-frequency trading strategies, started participating sign=
ificantly in the Treasury cash market. In 2019, for example, PTFs represent=
ed around 60 percent of the volume on the inter-dealer broker (IDB) platfor=
ms in the Treasury markets.
In essence, these PTFs and other firms are acting in a manner consistent wi=
th dealers in the securities markets. Nevertheless, despite these firms act=
ing as de facto market makers, and despite their regularity of participatio=
n consistent with buying and selling securities or government securities =
=E2=80=9Cas a part of a regular business,=E2=80=9D a number of these firms =
have not registered with the Commission as dealers.
This deprives investors and the markets themselves of important protections=
=E2=80=94protections that benefit market integrity, resiliency, transparenc=
y, and more.

I suppose there is some truth to this, that the trading business of making =
