treet Journal reports</a>=C2=A0that =E2=80=9CNeumann courted a group of WeW=
ork=E2=80=99s largest creditors to try and convince them that they should s=
upport his efforts to line up a bid for the company, but they declined, acc=
ording to people familiar with the talks.=E2=80=9D Did that group include S=
oftBank Group Corp.? I feel like if I ran SoftBank=E2=80=99s WeWork investm=
ent at this point, I would sell it all to Adam Neumann for $1 and a legally=
 binding promise that I would never hear from him again.</p>
