m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  times</a> last year about a dumb=
 story from Sam Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s internship at Jane Street, where he=
 kept making the maximum bet on slightly favorable coin flips, and I was li=
ke =E2=80=9Cwell that=E2=80=99s not very Kelly is it.=E2=80=9D But probably=
 I was wrong. Jane Street interns were limited to losing $100 per day, so I=
 sort of took $100 to be the size of his bankroll and thought he was aggres=
sive to bet it all on a 51% coin flip. But readers pointed out, no, come on=
, his=C2=A0<em>net worth=C2=A0</em>at the time was not $100; $100 was nothi=
ng to him even though it was all he could bet that day. As a percentage of =
his=C2=A0<em>actual bankroll=C2=A0</em>that was a fine bet.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway here is a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/34269974.257392/aHR0cHM6Ly9jYXBpdGFsZ2FpbnMudGh=
